name: INStartCallIntentResponseCode
desc: Constants that indicate the response state.

items.name: case unspecified
items.desc: A response code that indicates an unknown state.

items.name: case ready
items.desc: A response code that indicates app readiness.

items.name: case continueInApp
items.desc: A response code that indicates your app extension is ready to transfer control to the app to start the call.

items.name: case userConfirmationRequired
items.desc: A response code that indicates the user must confirm the call information before starting the call.

items.name: case failure
items.desc: A response code that indicates you were unable to perform the search.

items.name: case failureRequiringAppLaunch
items.desc: A response code that indicates the user must launch your app to start a call.

items.name: case failureCallingServiceNotAvailable
items.desc: A response code that indicates your app’s calling service isn’t currently available.

items.name: case failureContactNotSupportedByApp
items.desc: A response code that indicates the app doesn’t support the specified contact.

items.name: case failureAirplaneModeEnabled
items.desc: A response code that indicates the call can’t start due to the user’s device being in airplane mode.

items.name: case failureUnableToHandOff
items.desc: A response code that indicates the app can’t hand off the call.

items.name: case failureAppConfigurationRequired
items.desc: A response code that indicates the user must perform additional configuration steps before creating a call is possible.

items.name: case failureCallInProgress
items.desc: A response code that indicates the current call failed.
